Alan Cox <alan@redhat.com> wrote:
> 	spin_lock(&foo->lock);
> 	writel(0, &foo->regnum);
I presume there only needs to be an mmiowb() here if you've got the
appropriate CPU's I/O memory window set up to be weakly ordered.
> 	writel(1, &foo->data);
> 	mmiowb();
> 	spin_unlock(&foo->lock);
